<title>Baboon&apos;s ss&apos;o |a and hair used as charms against illness</title>
<summary><i>...further described the value attached, by the Bushmen, to Ss’ó/õä found in the possession of Baboons; also its great use to the latter. The hair of the Baboon considered as a charm (L V.-24. 5957-5967). </i>Baboons keep Ssho |oa (ss&apos;o |a) in their cheek, which people take out and keep when they kill them. They believe that this stick of Ssho |oa prevents the baboon from feeling pain and illness. Baboons live long and don&apos;t know illness, but if they do get ill it is severe and kills them.</summary><comments>1) Ss&apos;o-|a is also spelt  Ssho |oa, 2) p.5956v: Dia!kwain&apos;s father (Xaa-ttin) told him that ss&apos;o-|a is kept in the baboon&apos;s left cheek, 3) p.5963v: see <i>Chippings made by Dia!kwain&apos;s father (before the time of the &apos;Boers&apos;)</i>, 4) p.5964v: Dia!kwain&apos;s father (Xaa-ttin) told him most of this story; the rest is from Dia!kwain&apos;s personal experience, 5) See also <i>Baboons speak Bushman and have wives</i>, 6) This story is found in Book V-24</comments><date>6 February 1876 (started)</date><storypages>5957-5973</storypages><category>Custom and daily life</category><category>Plants and animals</category><author>Dia!kwain (David Hoesar) (V)</author><keyword><kw>baboon</kw><subkw>its Ssho |oa and hair is used as a charm against illness</subkw></keyword>
